## Validation

### Never use Valibot or Zod

This project uses **TypeBox / `Elysia.t`** exclusively. Valibot and Zod are not installed and must not be added.

```ts
// ❌ Wrong
import { z } from 'zod'
import { v, object, string } from 'valibot'

// ✅ Correct
import { t } from 'elysia'
import { createInsertSchema } from 'drizzle-typebox'
```

### Never trust client input

All input that arrives from a client (request body, query params, path params, headers, cookies) must be validated before use. TypeBox validation via Elysia handles this automatically in route definitions — but business logic validation (Step 2) is always written explicitly in the handler.

### Never validate only on the client

Client-side form validation is for UX only. Server-side TypeBox validation is the enforcing layer. Both must exist.

